# dagr code owners.
#
# Assigns review ownership so every pull request requires an owner's review
# before merge (see CONTRIBUTING.md "Review and merge"). This satisfies the
# arch.md commitment that the acceptance-criteria matrix and release checklist
# are "version-controlled and reviewed like code," and that additions to the
# core crate's dependency set are reviewed as API decisions.
#
# The wildcard rule covers the whole repository, so any PR — touching code or
# docs — reaches an owner. More specific rules may be layered below later
# (last-matching-pattern wins, per GitHub's CODEOWNERS semantics).
#
# NOTE: GitHub honours this file at .github/CODEOWNERS, CODEOWNERS (repo root),
# or docs/CODEOWNERS. It only *enforces* required review when branch protection
# with "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled in the repository settings —
# an operator action outside this repository. The recorded standing exception
# (the operator runs the ticket loop with autonomous merge) lives in
# docs/implementation/DEVIATIONS.md.

# Repository-wide owner.
